<br>
Extended Enhancement-type effects, including the 8th Coldain shawl, don't work on spells under a set duration (I can't remember what it is; it might be 20 minutes or 40 minutes or something around there). That means, with spellcasting reinforcement mastery, your heals over time will last for 24 seconds (normal duration) plus 12 seconds (50% extension) for a total of 36 seconds - 6 tics of healing bursts.<br>
<br>
Basically, Spellcasting Reinforcement Mastery will affect *any* buff you cast, including Yaulp, celestial healing, resists, spellcasting haste, pacify ... It doesn't affect Divine Aura or Divine Barrier though. Anything an hour or so long, like HP/AC buffs, will also get the benefit of the extended enhancement.<br>
<br>
If you use heals over time a lot, I highly recommend getting Spellcasting Reinforcement Mastery.. it essentially means *every* heal over time you cast will last 50% longer, and will do 50% more healing. That's a lot more than Healing Adept will do with instant-cast heals, and you can count on it every time, unlike the occasional crit heal from Healing Gift. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
